<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Empty Points Demo
</Paragraph>


<Paragraph>Essential Chart provides support for Empty Points. The data collection that is passed to the chart may have NaN or infinite values that will be considered as empty points. Users can also turn on or off empty points visibility.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\Empty Points Demo.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>
<Paragraph  FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16" TextAlignment="Center">
Fig: <Bold> Empty Points Demo </Bold>
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features:
</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem><Paragraph>Allows empty points to be displayed</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Provides an option for making a difference in empty points rendering, such as Symbol, Interior, and Symbol and Interior</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Allows setting an empty point's interior</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features:</Paragraph>

<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Palette"</Bold> helps to apply palette for ChartArea.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>Use the <Bold>"Show Empty Points"</Bold> check box to show or hide empty points. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Empty Point Style"</Bold> helps in selecting a style when rendering empty points.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The Combo box <Bold>"Empty Point Interior"</Bold> helps in selecting the brushes for the empty points.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"Empty Point Value"</Bold> helps to set the empty point value.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The check box <Bold>"ShowDataLabels"</Bold> sets the visibility of DataLabels. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"AdornmentsPosition"</Bold> helps to choose the position of DataLabels in the series segment. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"HorizontalAlignment"</Bold> helps to choose the position of DataLabels horizontally. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The combo box <Bold>"VerticalAlignment"</Bold> helps to choose the position of DataLabels vertically. </Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>

</FlowDocument>